## Install tewaks tool for GUI

- **gnome-shell-extensions** for to install gnome extensions

- **chrome-gnome-shell** for to download && install extensions from chrome ***GNOME Shell integration*** extensions
  - **plank** for dash to plank.
- **gnome-tweaks** for to manage GUI theme, extensions, shell and more.

```bash
sudo apt install gnome-shell-extensions chrome-gnome-shell gnome-tweaks
```

</br>

---

## Setup MERN Stack

In this section, we need to setup ***nodejs*** for core technology and ***mongodb*** for NoSQL database

</br>

### Install NodeJs

</br>

> - **M**ongoDB for database
> - **E**xpress for backend framework
> - **R**eact for frondend librarie
> - **N**odeJs for core technology
>
> We need to install **nodejs** and also use **yarn** instead of **npm** package mananger

</br>

```bash
# Download nodejs lts version (current is 16)
curl -fsSL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_16.x | sudo -E bash -

# Install nodejs
apt install -y nodejs

# Install development tools to build native addons
apt install -y gcc g++ make

# Download yarn package mananger
curl -sL https://dl.yarnpkg.com/debian/pubkey.gpg | gpg --dearmor | sudo tee /usr/share/keyrings/yarnkey.gpg >/dev/null
echo "deb [signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/yarnkey.gpg] https://dl.yarnpkg.com/debian stable main" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/yarn.list

# Install yarn
apt update && apt install -y yarn
```

Check nodejs, npm and yarn version

```bash
# Check node version
node -v

# Check npm version
npm -v

# Check yarn version
yarn -v
```

If no error, let go ***MongoDB*** for NoSQL database.

</br>

### Install MongoDB

</br>

>This tutorial reference from official [MongoDB](https://docs.mongodb.com/manual/tutorial/install-mongodb-on-ubuntu/) doucmentation
>
> - [Install lts community Edition version(current is 5.0)](#install-mongodb-community-edition)
> - [Run MongoDB Community Edition](#run-mongodb-community-edition)
> - [Configuration for systemd (systemctl) init system](#configuration-for-systemd-systemctl-init-system)
>
> - [Configuration for System V (service) init system](#configuration-for-system-v-service-init-system)

</br>

#### Install MongoDB community Edition

</br>

```bash
# Install gnupg
apt install gnupg

# Import the MongoDB public GPG Key
wget -qO - https://www.mongodb.org/static/pgp/server-5.0.asc | sudo apt-key add -

# Create the sources list mongodb file
echo "deb [ arch=amd64,arm64 ] https://repo.mongodb.org/apt/ubuntu focal/mongodb-org/5.0 multiverse" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/mongodb-org-5.0.list

# Reload local package database.
apt update

# Install the MongoDB packages version 5.0
apt install -y mongodb-org
```

</br>

Optional. Specify any available version of MongoDB, apt will upgrade the packages when a newer version becomes available. To prevent unintended upgrades, you can pin the package at the currently installed version:

```bash
echo "mongodb-org hold" | sudo dpkg --set-selections
echo "mongodb-org-database hold" | sudo dpkg --set-selections
echo "mongodb-org-server hold" | sudo dpkg --set-selections
echo "mongodb-org-shell hold" | sudo dpkg --set-selections
echo "mongodb-org-mongos hold" | sudo dpkg --set-selections
echo "mongodb-org-tools hold" | sudo dpkg --set-selections
```

</br>

#### Run MongoDB Community Edition

</br>

>Run th following command to check your operating system's built-in init system.
>
> ```bash
> # Check init system
> ps --no-headers -o comm 1
> ```
>
> - If result will be `systemd`, follow to the [***systemd (systemctl)*** section](#for-systemd-systemctl-init-system)
> - Or result will be `service`, follow to the [***System V (service)*** section](#for-systemd-systemctl-init-system)
>

</br>

### Configuration for systemd (systemctl) init system

```bash
# Start MongoDB
systemctl start mongod

# Enable MongoDB
systemctl enable mongod
```

</br>

> ***If you not get error; skip this step***

- [ ] if you get error like this ~ `Failed to start mongod.service: Unit mongod.service not found.`

```bash
# Run the command
systemctl daemon-reload

# Then start mongodb
systemctl start mongod
```

</br>

> ***Skip this step, if you are systemd (systemctl) init system user***

</br>

### Configuration for System V (service) init system

```bash
# Start MongoDB
service mongod start
```
